For Ubuntu
->Go to http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/  index.html
-->Download jdK package for Java SE 8u91 / 8u92
-->go to download location and run the command for extract : tar xzvf jdk-8u91-linux-x64.tar.gz 
-->sudo mkdir -pv /usr/local/java
-->move extracted file to /usr/local/java :sudo mv jdk1.8.0_91 /usr/local/java/

Set Path variable as:

export JAVA_HOME=/usr/local/java/jdk1.8.0_91
export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:${PATH}

you are done 

check java -version
      javac -version

similiarly do for redhat

